    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Inlaid works comprising an alloy of copper, lead, tin, and zinc, used as a ground for inlaying with gold and silver. The handicraft originated in Bidar, Karnataka, India in the 14th century CE, during the rule of the Bahamani Sultans.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
